022/**
023 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#the-object-element">&lt;object&gt;</a>
024 * element.
025 *
026 * <p>
027 * The object element represents an external resource, which can be treated as an image, a nested browsing context,
028 * or a resource to be handled by a plugin. It is commonly used to embed multimedia content such as Flash applications,
029 * PDFs, images, videos, or other HTML documents. While historically used for plugins, modern web development often
030 * prefers more specific elements like img, video, audio, or iframe when appropriate.
031 *
032 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
033 * <p class='bcode w800'>
034 *    <jc>// PDF document</jc>
035 *    Object_ <jv>pdf</jv> = <jsm>object</jsm>()
036 *       .data(<js>"/documents/manual.pdf"</js>)
037 *       .type(<js>"application/pdf"</js>)
038 *       .width(<js>"600"</js>)
039 *       .height(<js>"800"</js>)
040 *       .children(<jsm>p</jsm>(<js>"Your browser doesn't support PDF viewing."</js>));
041 * 
042 *    <jc>// SVG image</jc>
043 *    Object_ <jv>svg</jv> = <jsm>object</jsm>()
044 *       .data(<js>"/images/diagram.svg"</js>)
045 *       .type(<js>"image/svg+xml"</js>)
046 *       .width(<js>"400"</js>)
047 *       .height(<js>"300"</js>);
048 * 
049 *    <jc>// Embedded HTML page</jc>
050 *    Object_ <jv>html</jv> = <jsm>object</jsm>()
051 *       .data(<js>"/external/page.html"</js>)
052 *       .type(<js>"text/html"</js>)
053 *       .width(<js>"100%"</js>)
054 *       .height(<js>"500"</js>);
055 * 
056 *    <jc>// Flash content (legacy)</jc>
057 *    Object_ <jv>flash</jv> = <jsm>object</jsm>()
058 *       .data(<js>"/media/animation.swf"</js>)
059 *       .type(<js>"application/x-shockwave-flash"</js>)
060 *       .width(<js>"800"</js>)
061 *       .height(<js>"600"</js>)
062 *       .children(
063 *          <jsm>param</jsm>().name(<js>"quality"</js>).value(<js>"high"</js>),
064 *          <jsm>param</jsm>().name(<js>"bgcolor"</js>).value(<js>"#ffffff"</js>),
065 *          <jsm>p</jsm>(<js>"Flash is not supported by your browser."</js>)
066 *       );
067 * 
068 *    <jc>// Image with fallback</jc>
069 *    Object_ <jv>image</jv> = <jsm>object</jsm>()
070 *       .data(<js>"/images/photo.jpg"</js>)
071 *       .type(<js>"image/jpeg"</js>)
072 *       .width(<js>"640"</js>)
073 *       .height(<js>"480"</js>)
074 *       .children(<jsm>img</jsm>().src(<js>"/images/fallback.jpg"</js>).alt(<js>"Photo"</js>));
075 * 
076 *    <jc>// With usemap for image map</jc>
077 *    Object_ <jv>mapped</jv> = <jsm>object</jsm>()
078 *       .data(<js>"/images/map.jpg"</js>)
079 *       .type(<js>"image/jpeg"</js>)
080 *       .usemap(<js>"#imagemap"</js>);
081 * </p>
082 *
083 * <p>
084 * The following convenience methods are provided for constructing instances of this bean:
085 * <ul class='javatree'>
086 *    <li class='jc'>{@link HtmlBuilder}
087 *    <ul class='javatree'>
088 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#object() object()}
089 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#object(Object, Object...) object(Object, Object...)}
090 *    </ul>
091 * </ul>
092 * </p>
093 *
094 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
095 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
096 * </ul>
097 */
098@Bean(typeName="object")
099@FluentSetters
100public class Object_ extends HtmlElementMixed {  // NOSONAR - Intentional naming.

103    * Creates an empty {@link Object_} element.

114   }

116   /**
117    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-object-data">data</a> attribute.
118    *
119    * <p>
120    * Specifies the URL of the resource to be embedded. This is the primary source of content
121    * for the object element.
122    *
123    * <p>
124    * The value can be of any of the following types: {@link URI}, {@link URL}, {@link String}.
125    * Strings must be valid URIs.
126    *
127    * <p>
128    * URIs defined by {@link UriResolver} can be used for values.
129    *
130    * @param data The URL of the resource to be embedded.
131    * @return This object.
132    */
133   public Object_ data(String value) {
134      attr("data", value);
135      return this;
136   }
137
